Find the second largest and second smallest element in an array without sorting.

Remove duplicates from an array (using HashSet or without extra space).

Find the missing number in an array of size N containing numbers 1 to N.

Find the pair of elements whose sum is equal to a target value (Two Sum problem).

Find the intersection of two sorted arrays.

Find the Union of two sorted arrays without duplicates.

Rotate an array by K positions – clockwise or anticlockwise.

Move all zeros to the end while maintaining the order of other elements.

Find the majority element (appears more than N/2 times) – using Moore’s Voting Algorithm.

Find the maximum sum subarray (Kadane’s Algorithm).

Find the length of the longest subarray with sum = K (positive numbers / with negatives).

Find the longest substring / subarray without repeating elements (Sliding Window).

Find the count of subarrays whose sum = K.

Check if an array is a subset of another array (using sorting + binary search or HashSet).

Merge two sorted arrays without extra space (Gap method / In-place merge).

Find duplicates in an array where elements range 0...n-1 (using visited marking / Floyd cycle).

Find the product of array elements except itself (without division).

Sort array of 0s, 1s, and 2s (Dutch National Flag algorithm).

Find the first repeating and first non-repeating element in an array.

Implement cyclic sort and explain scenarios where it’s useful (e.g., missing number, duplicate number).
